As to the institution of the courses under the first Temple, there is no need to say anything, because every one hath it before him, 1 Clu-on, xxiv. But under the second Temple there was indeed some difference, not as to the order of their courses, but as to their heads and families. Of which thing the Talmudists treat largely, and indeed not altogether from the purpose : let them comment in my stead:
